reviewText: I really hate how catchy the tunes are as I'll start singing "meow-moo, count by two" even if I'm not around my kids, but they love it so I guess I'll manage.  It seems like Sesame Street kicked it up a notch from the first volume in terms of more involved story-lines but my sons ages 3.5 and 20 months are still very engaged. I was particularly impressed by the mini skip-counting lesson in the first episode.
Not a good show
My daughter loves elmo the musical, we were sad to see the bit was no longer continued in later seasons
Perfect for our toddler that prefers the Elmo the Musical segment out of Seasame Street! All the musicals are very well done.
My 3 year old son loves it and that's good enough for me!!! Just as good as the first Elmo musical!
It's 5 episodes of elmo the musical. If your kids like that part of the show, they'll like this DVD. The episodes aren't any better or worse than others, to respond to the other review.
The first volume is much more entertaining than this one. These episodes (minus Mt. Everest) are fairly lame.
My daughter loves this.  She loves to dance to it.  Elmo is the best!!!!
Great music for my toddler, she watches it every week.
Very entertaining.  Lots of songs. Kid approved.
It's Elmo, and snappy music.  I even sing some of the songs myself, so cute!

Who'da thunk-it?  Elmo the Musical...

A furry red monster and show-tunes, what could be better?
Always good to have an Elmo video to watch with a toddler in the house.

My daughter loves the first elmo the musical so I wanted to get her the second one to have more of what she loves. This one is much more advanced with what shapes are called and numbers. She can't count and doesn't even know what a square is so counting to 20, cubes, and a rhombus can be rather confusing. At first she didn't like the video at all because of this, but now she dances and jumps when it comes on and sings with the 'kitty cows'.
Not too bad. Not my personal favorite, but my daughter seems to enjoy it
My 2 year old son super loves it!
Item came earlier than expected and was perfectly in tact!
My son loves it.  Great for car rides!

Elmo the musical is my child's favorite movie. He loves the songs and dancing and clapping along. There is also a series of books that go along with it that he loves. This is a great show and I recommend it for every toddler.
Grandson loves it.
Daughter loves it!
My toddler son lights up and loves dancing to these cute and creative musicals.

Its really entertaining even for the adult in the room. The little people enjoy and learn at the same time, shapes, counting, addition/subtraction and telling time. Highly recommend. My toddler twins watch it over and over
Lots of fun
My daughter and my granddaughter and I sing these songs in our heads@!!!  Meow Moo count by two!

My 16 month old son loves Elmo and dances to all the songs. I'm fairly certain we've watched it 20 times in the past week. The songs are very catchy and you will be singing them to yourself all day long.
My kid loves it. Catchy songs. I usually dislike elmo, but this one is enjoyable

Both of kids ages 1 and 3 love Elmo. My 3 year old is more familiar with Elmo the musical so I got the DVD  for her to enjoy in the car. My 1 year old ended up loving this DVD and learned all of the songs really fast. It's a definitely a good buy for little ones. They enjoy car rides now thanks to Elmo.
Wonderful DVD. My daughter loves that segment. Each one seems just long enough to do the job.
Son loves it!
My grand daughter loves it
Great video for my 10 month old baby!! She loves it.
very cute my kids love this movie
My daughter absolutely loves these!  Saves us a dinner when she's ready to leave but we're not and also on road trips ;)

Great purchase! You definitely get your money's worth. My daughter love it and is now singing along with Elmo. She's 2 years old and love Elmo, if your little one loves elmo this is a great one to add to the collection. I also recommend the Grouch land movie Elmo has. Enjoy!
grand daughter loves him

I'm not sure I personally love it but my toddler has watched it several times a week in the car for the past couple of months and still isn't bored with it. He is very into music and likes the songs and dancing. All of the skits have been featured on Sesame Street, so if you want an idea of what they're like, check them out there or on youtube.
my 2 year old is obsessed with this movie.
Elmo wins
She loves it. We've watched it a hundred times already (probably more) on road trips. She just keeps asking for it again and again. Thank you...?
we didn't enjoy
This is one of our favorites.  Our 2 year old grandson asks for it over many of the other Elmo DVD's.
Elmo the Musical always provides hours of good times for the kids.  A definite have if you have kids.

My soon to be 2year old loves Elmo and this DVD is a big hit. The episodes are full length episodes of just the Elmo the Musical portion seen on Sesame Street. Love how each episodes incorporates counting, shapes into the songs.
Cute show for Elmo lovers.
Scariest monster movie I've seen in a while.
My daughter loves it! She gets so excited and starts clapping when I turn it on!
$10 for one episode is a bit much!!
